text: Van Buren County is a county of the U.S. state of Arkansas. As of the 2020 census, the population was 15,796. The county seat is Clinton. The county was formed on November 11, 1833, and named for Martin Van Buren, 8th President of the United States (1837â€“1841). == References == Category:1833 establishments in Arkansas Territory
